text: Kim Bok-rae (born 3 May 1977) is a South Korean table tennis player. She competed in women's doubles at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, placing fourth. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1977 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female table tennis players Category:Olympic table tennis players of South Korea Category:Table tennis players at the 2004 Summer Olympics
